The family of the late gospel singer, Osinachi Nwachukwu, has revealed that the bride price given to them by the singer’s husband might be returned to his family soon. According to BBC Igbo, the family reportedly set the date for the burial of the late singer for June 25, 2022. According to reports gathered, Osinachi’s family discussed that she would be buried in her father’s compound at Isuochi, Abia State, not in her husband’s house. -Advertisement- Recall that the singer alleged died from injuries sustained from the physical abuse by her husband, after being on life support for two months before her demise. The Attorney-General of the Federation has filed 23-count charges against Peter Nwachukwu, the husband of late gospel singer. Nwachukwu was accused of emotional, verbal and psychological abuse contrary to section 14(1) of the VAP Act, 2015.